items.content_html: Currying is a functional programming technique that involves transforming a function that takes multiple arguments into a series of functions that take one argument each. In JavaScript, currying can be used to create more modular and reusable code. In this post, we'll explain what currying is, how to use it in JavaScript, and some SEO considerations to keep in mind when writing about currying.
